I am a 2nd year film production student at UCA in Farnham, Surrey.

We are currently in the process of trying to find extras for our film that we are shooting in sugar shack (the old pop world) in Portsmouth. Due to the brief we can only have people who are 18+ the dates we will be needing you are the 17th and 19th of November 9am-5pm, dress code will be club attire. As we are only students and have a very limited budget we won‚Äôt be able to pay you for this role but we will provide catering, as well as this you will be mentioned in the credits of the film and this will be submitted to film festivals. If you have any questions or are interested please email me via - maddiewest2006@icloud.com or private message me alternatively you can find me on instagram filmsbymads06.

Thank you.

topComments.text: So happy to pay for festivals but not cast or crew?
Avoid, they have no interest in paying for people's time, only fame.

Hello everyone,

My name is Kayuran Moodley, and I am the founder of KM PICTURES, a newly established mobile film production based in Chatsworth, Durban. I‚Äôm currently in the process of expanding my team and looking for dedicated individuals to join me on this creative journey.

At this stage, I am specifically looking for:
üé• Camera Operator ‚Äì someone passionate about cinematography, able to work creatively with mobile or professional cameras, and interested in learning and experimenting with visual storytelling.
‚úÇÔ∏è Video Editor ‚Äì someone skilled in editing, sound design, and color grading, with a good eye for pacing, emotion, and storytelling (experience in horror or suspense genres will be an advantage).

KM PICTURES was started with a simple but powerful goal ‚Äî to create meaningful stories from small beginnings, using whatever tools and talent we have available. I believe in teamwork, creativity, and growth. This is a zero-budget project for now, but it‚Äôs built on passion, vision, and the goal of developing something great together from the ground up.

I‚Äôm currently working on my latest film script, and I want to collaborate with individuals who are serious about learning, growing, and being part of a local production that has the potential to expand into something bigger.

If you‚Äôre a filmmaker, editor, or someone who simply loves the art of storytelling and wants to build a future in film, I would love to connect with you. Let‚Äôs grow this production together and create something unique in the South African film space.

üìç Preferred Location: Chatsworth / Durban (for easier travel and teamwork)
üíº Production: Mobile Film (Independent / Zero Budget)
üìû Contact: 061 046 3076

Let‚Äôs bring creativity to life ‚Äî together.
‚Äî Kayuran Moodley
Founder & Director
KM PICTURES üé•

items.title: Hello everyone,

sharedPost.text:
Hey guys! Just had my interview at Aspie; a group therapy organisation that helps, supports and provides a voice for those diagnosed with Asperger‚Äôs! There I got to share my experiences living with Asperger‚Äôs both as a person and actor, what it was like being Sam (a leading person/character who is on the autistic spectrum) in the recent horror film, Lazuzu, and advice that I would give to those wanting to be actors themselves! What really inspired me was how talented these people are. Not just in drama/acting but in different forms of sports and arts! Aspie really does incredible work and provides people not just a place of comfort but also a place where they can allow their talent to shine based on their skills and show them to the public. Listening to some of their stories (including Jess‚Äô) really made my day. I‚Äôm so proud of them of their courage and emotional and mental strength. The questions they are were really good and, hopefully, my answers were helpful for them. I‚Äôm hoping to pay another visit one day. So glad I went. Especially during the month of November (the month of spreading awareness on men‚Äôs mental health). Also, major thanks to Darren Goodwin of Frenchie Flicks for arranging this for me. Hopefully, I‚Äôll do more interviews like this. Will keep you guys posted on the video interview! Thanks!

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies and some kind of Art House Underground Movies. I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.

I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch

Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928

Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 

please ask for details.

Ideally looking for local actors with experience for the show element.

items.text:
Looking for two actors. Male and Female.

Unpaid roles. Free Food. Travel compensation included.

Date: 24th-27th November (Actor‚Äôs availability during these dates will be accounted for when scheduling) 

Location: York, UK, YO10

Project Title and Description: ‚ÄòHappy Birthday‚Äô

5-minute psychological drama student film. A grieving husband is baking a birthday cake for his late wife. His voice-over narration starts off bitter-sweat, then slowly reveals how he was the culprit of his wife‚Äôs death.

Themes: obsession and jealousy.

Looking for actors to play ‚ÄòHusband‚Äô and ‚ÄòWife‚Äô.

Husband (lead actor):

Age 60 - 70.

Husband is a cold, and calculated character. His actions and body language are very precise and intentional.

The role involves some intimacy (hugging Wife character, holding her hand), but this can and will be changed for the actor if they are uncomfortable with this.

Wife (supporting actress):

Age 50 - 60. 

Wife is a character that is portrayed through the romanticised memory of the Husband character. This is a small role where there will be a lot of extreme close ups, rendering her almost anonymous.

The role involves some intimacy (being hugged from behind by Husband character, holding his hand), but this can and will be changed for the actor if they are uncomfortable with this.

Submission method:

Please email lisaalaba@gmail.com with your name, age, a headshot/selfie and the role you‚Äôre applying for. Please also confirm your responses to the pre-screening questions listed below.

A CV and a few lines for why you‚Äôd like to work on this project are not necessary, but helpful. 

If you are available on only two out of the four days, for example, please don‚Äôt hesitate to reach out anyway. Availability of actors will be accounted for during the scheduling process.

We will go through the script and character work after selection so there‚Äôs no need for a self-tape. However, again, please send any particular work that you think would be relevant to the role.

Pre-screening questions:

Are you happy to respond to director‚Äôs notes during pre-production and filming? Yes/No

Are you available during the dates listed and okay with potential long shooting days? (e.g. 8 hour day with lunch break) If not, please list your availability and any other issues/concerns which will be accounted for during scheduling.

For the Husband role, do you own a plaid-button shirt and dark trousers? Yes/No

For the Wife role, do you own a kitchen apron? Yes/No

Apply by Saturday 15th November 12pm.

Attached is the casting call poster and the last page of the script to give applicants an idea of the story.

items.text:
Do you ever feel resistant to the business side of acting? You‚Äôre definitely not alone. It‚Äôs the part that I struggle the most with, but like it or not, it‚Äôs part of the journey. And it very often matters more than talent. 

In this video, my friend Jodie Bentley dives into the time-and-creativity struggle ‚Äî that frustrating loop where you want to create but tell yourself there‚Äôs no time, which leads to inaction or perfectionism. She also shares how recognising that ‚Äúno time‚Äù excuse can help break the cycle and bring the joy back into creating.

üé• Watch the video here: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XzDLqLTATCk](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XzDLqLTATCk)

items.text:
Hey everyone! My name is Jackson Smith and I'm a fourth year at CU Boulder working on my BFA thesis film! I'm looking to fill two lead rolls if anyone is interested:

Title: Intersection

Genre: Drama

Logline: The film follows three people who unexpectedly effect each other while trying to make their way through a normal day. Introspective and character-focused. Very open to collaboration!

Roles: 

**Kat (Female, ~18-24)**: A young adult trying to find her footing. Kat often finds herself pushing forward in an attempt to forget what is behind her. She has a troubled relationship with her mother and has not been in contact with her for some time. It is now the day of her mother's birthday and Kat feels obligated to get her a cake.

**Heather (Female, 30s/40s)**: Kat's mother, independent and headstrong. Currently working as a freelance consultant, she really had to hustle to get to where she is now. However, her success came at the cost of her personal relationships. Heather wishes she and her daughter could reconnect, but she's not sure how to go about it. It is now Heather's birthday.

Production Type: Student

Contact Information: jasm4113@colorado.edu, (720)525-9544

Run Time: Short, ~12 minutes

Compensation: Unpaid (there will be food)

Union Status: Non-Union

Shooting Schedule: Rehearsal on Friday the 21st, shooting on the 22nd and 23rd of November

Filming Location: Boulder, Pearl Street

The International Conference "Performing Arts Between Tradition & Contemporaneity" was founded in 2003 to create a space for serious dialogue between traditional performance practices and contemporary artistic innovation. 

Over 22 editions, it has become a respected gathering point for performing arts professionals worldwide who refuse to see tradition and innovation as opposing forces, but rather as complementary elements in a living, evolving artistic practice.

Dates: December 18-22, 2025

Location: Schloss Laubegg, Austria

Capacity: Approximately 50 participants

Read More: https://www.nipai.org/post/22nd-performing-arts-conference  .

items.text:
Hi everyone!

**CASTING CALL** for a student short film planning to shoot in Berlin late February/early March.

**Logline:** An ambitious and emotionally detatched student gets a phone call that shatters her to the core, forcing her to be vulnerable. 

The film portrays themes of womanhood, loss, crisis and heartbreak.

If you fit any of the roles and are interested in the project, email your CV and headshot to **minnads67@gmail.com**. 

Looking forward to hearing from you!ü§ç

Hi! We are LOOKING FOR MALE ACTORS for a short film here in Budapest, set during World War II, and we aim to shoot over 2 days in late February 2025 in the H≈±v√∂sv√∂lgy area.

The title for the film is KITART√ÅS. It is a short film set during the Siege of Budapest and is a psychological exploration of the raw emotional cost in war times. The story follows Hungarian soldiers as they face a moral and physical struggle for survival in the last year of the war in Hungary. All roles require fluency in both English (for crew communication/rehearsals) and Hungarian (as the film's dialogue will be in Hungarian).

We are looking for people to play the following roles.

MIKL√ìS:

Character Description: A young Hungarian field medic who carries no weapon. Mikl√≥s is haunted and fragile, facing a moral and physical struggle to survive as his faith in the war collapses around him.

Requirements:

Male, 20‚Äì25 years old.

Must speak fluent English and Hungarian.

Comfortable performing in outdoor winter conditions.

√ÅD√ÅM:

Character Description: A Hungarian soldier under Istv√°n‚Äôs command. √Åd√°m is a man torn between obedience to his orders and the stirrings of his own conscience and guilt. His internal conflict becomes a major turning point in the film.

Requirements:

Male, 25‚Äì30 years old.

Must speak fluent English and Hungarian.

Comfortable performing in outdoor winter conditions.

Strong dramatic ability and emotional range.

If you would like to be considered, please send your headshots, short introduction, and (if available) a showreel or acting CV to:

‚úâÔ∏è contactingdianag@gmail.com

I am a 2nd year film production student at UCA in Farnham, Surrey.

We are currently in the process of trying to find extras for our film that we are shooting in sugar shack (the old pop world) in Portsmouth. Due to the brief we can only have people who are 18+ the dates we will be needing you are the 17th and 19th of November 9am-5pm, dress code will be club attire. As we are only students and have a very limited budget we won‚Äôt be able to pay you for this role but we will provide catering, as well as this you will be mentioned in the credits of the film and this will be submitted to film festivals. If you have any questions or are interested please email me via - maddiewest2006@icloud.com or private message me alternatively you can find me on instagram filmsbymads06.

Thank you.

We are casting for an updated tour of the children‚Äôs theatre show, ‚ÄúThe Dinosaur That Pooped a Rock Show‚Äù, based on the popular books by McFly‚Äôs Tom Fletcher and Dougie Poynter. 

The show is written and directed by Miranda Larson with songs and music by Tom Fletcher & Dougie Poynter and Barrie Bignold and is produced by Mark Thompson at MT Productions. 

**Production dates:**

Auditions will take place on 24th November 2025

Rehearsals begin on 12th January ‚Äì 22nd January 2026 in London
Tour dates Jan ‚Äì Nov 2026.
We are currently have 91 dates and counting. 

**Production location: **Greater London

**Role: **We are looking for a costume character/ skin artist to play the role of Dino. The artist will need to operate Dino‚Äôs mouth, hands and head, bringing the character to life. They will also be required to join in dance moves and routines whilst inside the costume. We are looking for someone between 5‚Äô6‚Äù and 5‚Äô10‚Äù tall. Previous skin/ costume character experience is essential.

The successful applicant will need to have a full UK drivers licence and will be comfortable driving the touring van on a shared basis with the rest of the company.

Please send CV's & headshots to: casting.mtproductions@gmail.com

**Fees:**

Rehearsal fee: ¬£550pw

Show day fee: ¬£150

Travel day fee: ¬£50

Subsistence: ¬£20

items.text:
Hi friends! I have a question for the group (especially for agents and casting, but also anyone)! I started acting seriously 20 years ago, when I was a kid. I started in theatre, have impressive training/education, pivoted to film 10 years ago, then took an extensive break. Last year I recommitted and spent a fair amount of time reacquainting myself with the industry and where it is. Updated headshots, portfolio shots, resume, self tape equipment, renewed memberships to the three main casting resources, etc. This year I booked a couple of live performances and a whole bunch of commercial work, several featured background, a costar, a short film lead, a short film supporting, and im about to film my first vertical as a supporting role. Here‚Äôs my issue/question:

I know we are heading into a slow season and I wanted to use this time to focus on getting representation. BUT I‚Äôve only seen one project. I don‚Äôt have a reel and that‚Äôs kind of important. I have a decent resume, imdb credits, and have made a lot of connections this year. I‚Äôve put a ‚Äúreel‚Äù together of past self tape clips, but I really need some professional footage. I‚Äôm not sure what to do. Is it appropriate to email production for footage? If so, how long after filming should I wait before asking? If not, or if footage isn‚Äôt available yet, what is the most professional thing to do? Specifically focusing on what agents/agencies would prefer. 

Thanks for any help!

üé¨** FLERE medvirkende s√∏ges til kortfilm for **Foreningen Lige Adgang

I forbindelse med mit speciale, udvikler jeg en r√¶kke **kortfilm i samarbejde med Foreningen Lige Adgang**, der vises som en del af deres workshops og opl√¶g om **antidiskrimination **‚Äì optagelser i K√∏benhavn.

Vi har allerede en r√¶kke medvirkende, som har meldt sig p√• - men **vi har brug for endnu flere** til denne vigtige sag!

Vi s√∏ger medvirkende, der vil dele deres perspektiver ‚Äì **uanset om du har etnisk minoritetsbaggrund eller er allieret** ‚Äì som vil bidrage til en vigtig samtale om trivsel, inklusion og ligestilling.

Du **beh√∏ver ingen filmisk erfaring** ‚Äì kun lyst til at bidrage til en vigtig samtale.

Det vigtigste er, at du har lyst til at dele dine tanker eller erfaringer og v√¶re med til at skabe film, der kan g√∏re en forskel.

**Fokus p√• tryghed og inkluderende deltagelse:**
* Filmene udvikles gennem workshops, hvor du som deltager har **medindflydelse og ejerskab** over processen og fort√¶llingen
* Vi arbejder med **l√∏bende samtykke**, og du godkender altid materialet, f√∏r noget deles
* **Alle medvirkende krediteres som medskabere** i filmen 

Temaer, vi arbejder med:
üí¨ Hvad vil det sige at v√¶re en god allieret?
üîÅ Hvad hvis rollerne var byttet om?

üìç Optagelser i K√∏benhavn 
üìÖ Vi optager om dagen disse datoer: Torsdag d. **20. november** + mandag d. **24. november **+ tirsdag d. **25. november** (men **du beh√∏ver ikke at kunne alle dage**!)
ü•ó Forplejning er inkluderet

Vi √∏nsker et **mangfoldigt cast **og opfordrer alle til at melde sig ‚Äì uanset k√∏n, seksualitet, alder, etnicitet, religion, faglig baggrund eller funktionsevne.

Skriv til mig via **malene.juell@gmail.com** eller en direkte besked med:
* Hvilke(n) af dagene du kan
* Hvorfor du √∏nsker at medvirke
* Gerne et billede af dig selv

‚Äî

**Malene Juell-Hansen** (specialestuderende p√• Film- og medievidenskab, K√∏benhavns Universitet)

üìç Optagelser i K√∏benhavn 
üìÖ Vi optager om dagen disse datoer: Torsdag d. **20. november** + mandag d. **24. november **+ tirsdag d. **25. november** (men **du beh√∏ver ikke at kunne alle dage**!)
ü•ó Forplejning er inkluderet

Vi √∏nsker et **mangfoldigt cast **og opfordrer alle til at melde sig ‚Äì uanset k√∏n, seksualitet, alder, etnicitet, religion, faglig baggrund eller funktionsevne.

Skriv til mig via **malene.juell@gmail.com** eller en direkte besked med:
* Hvilke(n) af dagene du kan
* Hvorfor du √∏nsker at medvirke
* Gerne et billede af dig selv

‚Äî

**Malene Juell-Hansen** (specialestuderende p√• Film- og medievidenskab, K√∏benhavns Universitet)

I samarbejde med Foreningen Lige Adgang

items.text:
Hello üëã

The Indie film scene is great fun, an incredible learning experience, myself and a producer I've worked with have decided to punch up to get a proper feature film on streaming services

It's a psychological horror that delves into many modern social problems - identity, betrayal, revenge, stalking, voyeurism, abusive relationship dynamics, manipulation, and more

This will not be a low grade production, will be shot professionally, with a full film crew, edited, colour graded and released on streaming services with a clear view to make money 

Pay will be on a sweat equity basis (we all own a share of the film and therefore the same share of the royalties), so the better we all perform the more we get paid

As such - if you are an actor who is looking to deliver a performance that is very visceral and real, and have been looking to be a main/supporting role in a full feature, feel free to apply via Mandy or pop me or JugganortFilms a message

Please be absolutely sure if you are applying, there are different roles and some are main cast - you must be completely free over February 2026, determined, enthusiastic, capable of delivering a serious role over many days of filming 

Food/drink will be provided to all cast and crew and accommodation can be arranged on set if needed 

https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3044100/watching/

Attached is a pitch video to give an idea of theme and feel 

We look forward to hearing from you üìΩÔ∏èüéûÔ∏èüé¨

items.summary:
Hello üëã

The Indie film scene is great fun, an incredible learning experience, myself and a producer I've worked with have decided to punch up to get a proper feature film on streaming services

It's a psychological horror that delves into many modern social problems - identity, betrayal, revenge, stalking, voyeurism, abusive relationship dynamics, manipulation, and more

This will not be a low grade production, will be shot professionally, with a full film crew, edited, colour graded and released on streaming services with a clear view to make money 

Pay will be on a sweat equity basis (we all own a share of the film and therefore the same share of the royalties), so the better we all perform the more we get paid

As such - if you are an actor who is looking to deliver a performance that is very visceral and real, and have been looking to be a main/supporting role in a full feature, feel free to apply via Mandy or pop me or JugganortFilms a message

Please be absolutely sure if you are applying, there are different roles and some are main cast - you must be completely free over February 2026, determined, enthusiastic, capable of delivering a serious role over many days of filming 

Food/drink will be provided to all cast and crew and accommodation can be arranged on set if needed 

https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3044100/watching/

Attached is a pitch video to give an idea of theme and feel 

We look forward to hearing from you üìΩÔ∏èüéûÔ∏èüé¨

items.text:
**CALL FOR SOUND & LIGHTING BOARD Operators**

**Production:** *George Orwell‚Äôs 1984*
**Produced by:** PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS
**Location:** Three Stories Theater
937 Liberty Ave, Downtown Pittsburgh
**Performances:** December 4‚Äì7, 2025
**Contact:** playboxpgh@gmail.com

**PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS** is seeking a **Sound Board Operator** and a **Lighting Board Operator** for our upcoming production of *1984* by George Orwell, directed by M.A.C. This is a new concept for this story, completely Americanized through costumes, set design, sound, and overall aesthetic.

Our **full cast and crew of over 30 people** have already been hard at work bringing this show to life over the past few months. We have a complete design and stage management team in place; we are now looking for skilled operators to help us execute this ambitious and timely production during tech week and performances.

**POSITION DETAILS**
**Titles:** Sound Board Operator and Lighting Board Operator
**Compensation Type:** Volunteer / Possible post-show stipend
*(We want to be transparent: this is a volunteer position, but if funds allow, a small stipend may be available after the production.)*

**Dates & Commitment:**
* **Rehearsals (all optional for operators):** Sundays, 6‚Äì9 PM starting August 3, 2025
Trust Arts Education Center ‚Äî 807 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA
* **Tech Week:** November 24 ‚Äì December 3, 2025 (dark day on Thanksgiving) ‚Äî 937 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA
* **Performances:** December 4‚Äì7, 2025 (5 performances total)
Three Stories Theater ‚Äî 937 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA

We‚Äôre happy to work with your schedule. Please include any known conflicts when reaching out.

**QUALIFICATIONS**
* For Sound: Experience with QLab or a similar playback system
* For Lighting: Familiarity with ETC lighting consoles preferred
* Reliable, communicative, and calm under pressure
* Comfortable collaborating with an awesome stage management and design team! 

**TO APPLY**
Please email **playboxpgh@gmail.com** with:
* Resume (or a brief summary of your relevant experience) **This is super important, since we are using a Pittsburgh Cultural Trust space. They require a review of your resume to let you use the theatre tech equipment.*
* Availability during tech week and performances

If interested, we‚Äôll be in touch right away to discuss next steps.

Thank you!

Marc Palombo
PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS

sharedPost.text:
I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies and some kind of Art House Underground Movies. I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.

I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch

Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928

Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 

please ask for details.

Appearance: Refined, tall, effortlessly stylish ‚Äî always immaculately put together, but never loud. Think classic tailoring, muted tones, the kind of man who makes minimalism look regal.

Voice & Presence: Calm, articulate, with dry humor and a quiet authority that commands attention without raising his voice.

Personality:

Julian is the embodiment of composure in chaos. A seasoned creative who‚Äôs seen the industry‚Äôs highs and lows, he moves through the fashion world with both elegance and discernment. He believes beauty should mean something ‚Äî that clothing is more than fabric, it‚Äôs language. 

Unpaid - Meal, Copy, Credit

Nov 18th or 19th

4 hours Max of work

Personal Short Film Project

SEEKING 2 ACTORS FOR MAIN CAST

WHEN: Dec 20‚Äì23, 2025

PAID: CAD $150 / Day

Project Title:

The Thought Experiment ‚ÄúMETA MONTAGE‚Äù

Genre:

Meta-psychological Drama / Experimental Metafiction / Postmodern Romance

Logline:

When a screenwriter finds himself inside the very film he‚Äôs writing, reality and fiction intertwine ‚Äî forcing him, his characters, and even the audience to confront the question: Who is truly creating whom?

A visual and interactive interpretation of the Multiverse Theory.

Production Details:

Dates: December 20‚Äì23, 2025

Location: Vancouver, BC

Rate: CAD $150 / day

Type: Independent Short Film (non-union, paid)

Casting:

JACK (30s)

An expressive man in his 30s. Starts as a victim tied to a chair but gradually becomes both the actor and writer of the film. Moves between fiction and reality, showing layers of vulnerability and control.

Keywords: Actor / Writer / Victim / Meta-role

Look: Half-dressed, sweaty, bloody ‚Üí later calm and casual.

NARRATOR (30s‚Äì40s)

A calm, mysterious man in a classic suit. Both inside and outside the film, he speaks directly to the camera as a philosophical observer. His emotions slowly break through his composed tone.

Keywords: Narrator / Observer / Director-like

Look: Formal, mustache, black & white lighting, under spotlight.

I‚Äôll be sending those who emailed me a 6-minute short film I recently shot, along with a script excerpt from the project.

I‚Äôd really appreciate it if you could send me a video of yourself reading the script by November 23

Contact:

Director / Writer / Producer : Yuri Kakuya

üìß hkjfilm@gmail.com

Hi everyone! I'm casting a **voice over commercial **for StatsCan, and we are looking for people (men and women, 25-75 years old) that can speak **Inuktitut. **These ads will run across TV, Web and Radio.

If you're interested in auditioning, please email me at: **adriennelindsaycasting@gmail.com** for details. I will send you the script of an ad we did a few years ago. To audition, you will need to record yourself reading the ad and send it in to me. We are looking for "official-sounding" reads.

**Specs**:

South Baffin (Inuktitut Nunavut) dialect.
*Talent can be based anywhere, but will need access to a professional recording studio to patch in.*

Usage: voice over commercial - multiple spots across TV, Web and Radio. Open to both ACTRA & non-union performers.

Thank you!

**25th Anniversary Edition: International Physical Theatre Laboratory**

**December 13‚Äì22, 2025 | Schloss Laubegg, Austria**

*A transformative nine-day intensive bringing together theatre artists, dancers, choreographers, circus performers, and movement practitioners from around the world.*

The International Physical Theatre Laboratory has been a cornerstone of European physical theatre training since 2000, bringing together artists from around the world for intensive periods of artistic exchange, training, and creation. Organized by NIPAI (New International Performing Arts Institute), IPTL embodies the organization's mission to foster international collaboration and support the development of contemporary performance practices that transcend cultural and disciplinary boundaries.

Due to the intimate nature of the program and the desire to create a balanced, dynamic group, participation is limited to 15 artists. Selection is based on professional experience, artistic motivation, and the potential contribution each applicant can make to the collective laboratory experience.

**To learn more about the program, faculty, schedule, and practical details, visit: **

https://www.nipai.org/programs/international-physical-theatre-lab .
items.previewDescription: For performers and actors, dance and movement practitioners, professional artists and educators, theatre directors and stage professionals, as well as performing arts academics and students. Participants can receive a certificate upon completion.

Hey everyone,
I‚Äôm Michael Uchenik, a film student, and this December (11‚Äì16.12) I‚Äôll be shooting my graduation film in Berlin, a story that explores the connection between trauma, love, and the body.

The entire film takes place during a laid-back house chill party, a warm, vibrant space where something deeper quietly unfolds.
It tells the story of David, an Israeli man full of life on the outside but haunted by a trauma he can‚Äôt escape, and Leo, his German boyfriend who tries to love him hard enough to bring him back to the present.

It‚Äôs a film about the duality of what we show versus what we hide.
About love as an anchor, and how memories follow us even when we move far away.

I‚Äôm looking for open-minded people who feel comfortable in front of the camera and with their bodies to join as participants in the party scenes.
This is not a pornographic film, but a sensitive and artistic project that looks at intimacy and vulnerability in an honest way.

If this sounds interesting to you, here‚Äôs a link with more info.

https://forms.gle/ZZJw8THu6qSW6UoKA 

And please feel free to share it with anyone who might be a good fit üí´

Thank you so much,
Michael

Casting Call ‚Äì Lead Role ‚ÄúLil Messias‚Äù in Bachelor Film Groupies (The Norwegian Film School) - Paid! 

We are casting for Groupies, an ambitious and visually striking bachelor film by a talented team of students at The Norwegian Film School.

The film explores the groupie phenomenon through a music film about a rapper and a fangirl spending one surreal night backstage. Blending realism, stylization, and surreal imagery, Groupies delves into themes of power, status, gender roles, and what it truly means to be human in a superficial, image-driven world.

Role: Lil Messias (‚ÄúLil Mess‚Äù) ‚Äì Lead
Lil Messias is an internationally acclaimed rap artist.
On stage, he radiates confidence, sex appeal, and dominance ‚Äî the perfect image of modern masculinity.
Beneath the surface, however, he battles growing anxiety and emptiness in a life fueled by drugs, violence, and meaningless sex. He is trapped in his own image and longs to be truly seen. (Age 20-30)

This role involves:
 ‚Ä¢ An intimate scene with the character Ninni.
A professional intimacy coordinator will be attached to ensure a safe, respectful, and transparent process.
 ‚Ä¢ A rap performance, including recording a song and potentially some choreography.
 ‚Ä¢ The creative team will also be developing a full artist brand around the character ‚Äî an exciting opportunity to embody a complete on-screen persona.

Actors of all ethnicities and backgrounds are strongly encouraged to apply.

Production Details
 ‚Ä¢ Shooting period: Between January 20‚Äì30, 2025
 ‚Ä¢ Location: Norway
 ‚Ä¢ Compensation: According to Norwegian industry rates (Tariff)

Travel expenses will be covered. (Europe only)

If this sounds like something for you, please get in touch. Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Please send location, portrait and if you have: showreel and/or introduction tape.

Email: deteramalie@gmail.com

UPDATE: SUBMISSIONS ARE CLISING FOR NOW. THANK YOU EVERYONE WHO HAS SUBMITTED SO FAR. üôåüèΩ
______

üö® CASTING CALL ‚Äì FEATURE FILM üö® (RDE FILMS)

RDE Films is now accepting auditions for our upcoming feature film. We‚Äôre seeking bold, authentic performers with strong presence and emotional range. Following directions is extremely important to our process.

‚∏ª

AVAILABLE ROLES

Detective 1 ‚Äì Male, 25‚Äì35
Seasoned detective, weathered and street-smart with a strong personality.
Types: Jon Bernthal, Shia LaBeouf, Denzel Washington, Lakeith Stanfield, Benjamin Bratt.
Barrio-raised energy. (Willing to smoke fake herbal cigarettes.)

Detective 2 ‚Äì Male, 25‚Äì35
Experienced cop with a black-and-white view of justice.
Types: Lakeith Stanfield, Michael B. Jordan, Don Cheadle.
Raised in a good neighborhood; confident and disciplined.

Assistant District Attorney ‚Äì Male, 25‚Äì45
Strong personality, ‚Äúboss energy,‚Äù sharp and commanding. The quintessential lawyer type.

Killer ‚Äì Male, 30‚Äì45
Soft-spoken, intelligent, creepy, and quietly imposing.
Think Ed Gein, Arthur Fleck, Longlegs.

Racist Pastor ‚Äì Male, 35‚Äì55
Charismatic, silver-tongued, sly, and playful ‚Äî hides malice behind a smile.

Killer‚Äôs Mother ‚Äì Female, 40‚Äì60
Quiet, submissive, battered southern housewife. Soft-spoken and broken.

Killer‚Äôs Father ‚Äì Male, 40‚Äì60
Abusive, mean, southern personality. Stoic, intimidating, and abrasive.

Captain of Precinct ‚Äì Male, 35‚Äì65
Respectable, strong leader type. Endearing and commanding presence.

Missing Child ‚Äì Female, 10‚Äì13 
Smart, articulate, emotionally mature. Must be able to cry and portray broken emotion.

Missing Child‚Äôs Mother ‚Äì Female, 25‚Äì35
Loving, playful, fiery. Must portray grief, depression, and distraught emotion.

Angry Mother (Smoker Mom) ‚Äì Female, 25‚Äì35
Mean, vindictive, narcissistic with a bad attitude. (Willing to smoke fake herbal cigarettes.) Think of the mother from the movie ‚ÄúPrecious.‚Äù

Gang Leader ‚Äì Male, 30‚Äì40 (Latinx Preference)
Calm but powerful demeanor. Ex-convict type with commanding presence.
Ability to perform a Chicano accent required.

Detective 1‚Äôs Brother ‚Äì Male, 15‚Äì25
Barrio-raised, fiery, gang mentality. Must be comfortable with prop weapons near their face.

Creepy Teacher ‚Äì Male, 25‚Äì35
Friendly on the surface but disturbingly affectionate toward his students. Unsettling presence required.

‚∏ª

üì© HOW TO SUBMIT
CLOSED FOR NOW

items.text:
Still looking for volunteers for a Short film project who like to act in front of the camera.

The purpose of this short film is to create a new showreel for every actor and actress who‚Äôs gonna participate on it.

What's the movie supposed to be about?

A young man, once part of an underground operation supplying drugs to his boss, has since left the shady business to start a normal life.

Months later, he returns to the warehouse to surprise his former boss with a gift - but as he steps inside, he's struck by how much has changed. The familiar place now feels foreign, guarded, and tense.

After a brief, uneasy reunion, he runs into an old colleague, haunted by the past, does everything he can to avoid her before quickly leaving - closing the door on a life he's no longer part of.

Actors must be able to speak in English fluently!!

Open roles 

(Melly) Female, 18+

(Tasha) Female, 18+

(Maddie) Female, 18+

(Avi) Male, 45+

Extra 

Female & Male any ethnicity and 20+

For the spin

This will be shot in Cologne 

2 day between November 24-30 2025

If interested and available please send headshot to email officialemmanuelbenjamin@gmail.com
items.summary:
Still looking for volunteers for a Short film project who like to act in front of the camera.

The purpose of this short film is to create a new showreel for every actor and actress who‚Äôs gonna participate on it.

What's the movie supposed to be about?

A young man, once part of an underground operation supplying drugs to his boss, has since left the shady business to start a normal life.

Months later, he returns to the warehouse to surprise his former boss with a gift - but as he steps inside, he's struck by how much has changed. The familiar place now feels foreign, guarded, and tense.

After a brief, uneasy reunion, he runs into an old colleague, haunted by the past, does everything he can to avoid her before quickly leaving - closing the door on a life he's no longer part of.

Actors must be able to speak in English fluently!!

Open roles 

(Melly) Female, 18+

(Tasha) Female, 18+

(Maddie) Female, 18+

(Avi) Male, 45+

Extra 

Female & Male any ethnicity and 20+

For the spin

This will be shot in Cologne 

2 day between November 24-30 2025

If interested and available please send headshot to email officialemmanuelbenjamin@gmail.com

items.text:
Exciting News !
I'm thrilled to share my book EDDIE'S BACK -- A gripping story that I believe would make a FANTASTIC MOVIE.

I've already WRITTEN AND COPYRIGHTED THE SCREENPLAY, so it's ready to go! Now, I'm reaching out to production companies, literary agents, film agents, and directors who might be interested in bringing this story to life on the big screen.

EDDIE'S BACK - May 1963, Eddie a popular teenager is intentionally hit by a car, which leaves him in a coma. It's 2025, Eddie wakes up. He is shocked and disappointed at what he sees. Until the ghost of JFK visits him and inspires him to make a difference.

Now Eddie 77 years young, realizes why he was kept alive and what he has to do.

However, a senior Senator with an agenda of his own is watching Eddie's every move and is prepared to stop his mission at any cost.

DREAM CAST (Just Imagining!)
#HarrisonFord - #CandyClark - #PaulLeMat - #RichardDreyfuss - #CharlesSDutton - #MarkWahlberg - #MatthewMcConaughey - #MargotRobbie - #RobertDeniro - #BradleyCooper - #TaylorSwift - #MorganFreeman - #NicolasCage - #GregKinnear - #AnneHathaway - #WillFerrell - #PatrickSchwarzenegger - #joancollins -#kellyopsal -#islacervelli - #JackHyde -#LaurenSanchez -#jeffbezos -#elonmusk -#JordonHudson -#parishilton 
DIRECTOR - #RonHoward

NO OFFICIAL TIES - JUST PUTTING IT OUT THERE AND HOPING TO GET EDDIE'S BACK INTO THE RIGHT HANDS!

TAGGING TOP AGENCIES:
#ImagineEntertainment - #IndependentArtistGroup - #WilliamMorrisEndeavor - #VerveTalentandLiteraryManagement - #TheWayneAgency - #CAA
And indie powerhouses like: #A24 - #AnnapurnaPictures - #PlanBEntertainment - #BlumhouseProductions - #KillerFilms - #Neon - #FilmNation - #BleeckerStreet - #ElaraPictures - #BigBeach

NO OFFICIAL TIES - Just putting it out there and hoping to get EDDIE'S BACK into THE RIGHT HANDS!

PRODUCTION COMPANIES I ADMIRE:
#SONYPICTURES - #WARNERBROSDISCOVERY - #IMAGEENTERTAINMENT - #WALTDISNEYPICTURES

PRODUCERS - I'd love to work with:
#MarkCiardi - #MattDamon - #MarkWahlberg - #WillFerrell - #TomHanks

NO OFFICIAL TIES - Just putting it out there and hoping to get EDDIE'S BACK into THE RIGHT HANDS!

#Eddie'sBack #BooktoFilm #Screenplayready #Filmadaptation #Moviepitch #Filmmakers #producers #directors #Independentfilm #IndieCinema #literaryAgents

WHAT IF EDDIE (HARPER) AND JOHN (MILLER) WERE FRIENDS IN 1963?

Let's make movie magic happen!

PEOPLE WILL COME!

They haven‚Äôt stepped foot in a movie theater in 40 years.
Not since the golden days of double features and balcony seats.
But one day, without even knowing why‚Ä¶
THEY GET IN THEIR CAR AND GO

Not for the stadium seating.
Not for the surround sound.
**But for something deeper. Something they‚Äôve been missing.**

They walk into the lobby ‚Äî wide-eyed, hearts open, like children.
The smell of popcorn. The hum of the projector.
A moment suspended in time.

They don‚Äôt blink when the clerk says, ‚ÄúTwenty dollars.
Because this isn‚Äôt a transaction ‚Äî it‚Äôs a Homecoming.

They find their old seats‚Ä¶ the very ones from their childhood.
And the screen lights up with a story that speaks to the soul.

**Eddie‚Äôs Back** isn‚Äôt just a movie.
It‚Äôs a bridge across generations.
A story that blends nostalgia, humor, and hope ‚Äî with just enough magic to make you believe again.

They will laugh.
They will cry.
And most importantly‚Ä¶
**They will remember.**

Baby Boomers will come.
They will bring their children.
Their grandchildren.
And one day ‚Äî their great-grandchildren.

Because *Eddie‚Äôs Back* reminds them of what was good‚Ä¶
**And what can still be good again.**

The one constant through all the years has been family films ‚Äî
**Stories that bring us together.**

Oh yes ‚Äî people will come.
Not because they need to‚Ä¶ but because their hearts tell them to!
And when they do‚Ä¶
**They‚Äôll thank you for bringing it to life.**

items.text:
Casting call for "Warriors" a new Scottish musical.

This is a paid profit share production, more details to follow below.

The show follows 4 serving soldiers from 1 SCOTS who have just been posted to Colchester as part of 16 Air Assault Brigade, the soldiers have only recently passed their infantry training and are about to head off to Afghanistan.

It shows how these soldiers deal with life, love, death, relationships, homosexuality, substance abuse and the mundane day to day living and training for current operations in Afghanistan, as well as how going away affects those around them.

The show was previously performed at the Edinburgh Fringe Festival in 2023 with 5 star reviews, and again at the Oran Mor in Glasgow in August 2024.

We are looking for 5-6 strong male presenting singer-actors with some previous dance experience, playing age 22-30, to complete our cast and help bring this show to life through 2026. We are looking for cast members to take on the lead roles of the 4 soldiers as well as flexible performers who are willing to take on a swing/cover role in the production and learn 2 parts each. All covers/swings will be on standby for shows as well as getting confirmed dates on which they‚Äôll perform.

There will be a readthrough in December and weekly rehearsals on Wednesday nights in Glasgow, as well as the occasional extra rehearsal to be arranged once we have a full cast, starting in January. The first show is planned for 25th April 2026 in Gartcosh, we will then have performances in various social and miners clubs between April and August, leading up to a full Fringe run in 2026.

Several fundraisers are being organised to bring in funds throughout the year, which combined with ticket sales will go towards making sure each performer gets a decent profit share. We are also hoping to provide a larger share to each performer during the fringe, we are working hard to make sure the show is well advertised and it will help assure it‚Äôs well attended, we will however also rely on the performers to help with advertising and ticket sales.

There is a detailed breakdown on each character as well as audition details in the document below.

Audition tapes should be submitted by 23rd of November, with recalls the following week.

If you have any questions or wish to find out more, do not hesitate to get in touch either by private message or by email on: rajmundolahperforming@gmail.com

***CASTING FOR NATIVITY! THE MUSICAL***

Looking for musical theatre performers who are not doing panto but would still love to do a show this Christmas!!

We are producing a charity production of NATIVITY! THE MUSICAL here in Romford

We are looking for....

GORDON SHAKESPEARE (Male - playing age 30-45) Hugely competitive teacher at Oakmoor Prep School. Bari/Tenor vocals

LORD MAYOR / ENSEMBLE (Male - playing age 35-60)

MISS RYE / ENSEMBLE (Female - playing age 23-50)

THE CRITIC / ENSEMBLE (Any Gender - playing age 25-60)

HOLLYWOOD PRODUCER / ENSEMBLE (Any Gender - playing age 25-60)

Show runs 4-23 Dec 2025

Venue: Brookside Theatre Romford

Production: Charity musical

Rehearsals: Monday - Thursday daytimes / evenings by schedule

Remuneration: Flat Fee

Please PM for more info or email harri@brooksidetheatre.com
